        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 1:28AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 126 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm in
western San Saba County, south of Highway 190, moving south at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fredonia, Pontotoc, and Voca.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
